		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Maybe this was already addressed in the A53 thread, and since I don't know how the A53 mapper works, this might be a dumb suggestion.<br /><br />But if initilization is such a big issue, would it be terribly hard for the A53 menu to initialize all 8 RAM pages and relevant registers to zero during its routine for starting up a game?<br />While this of course differs between emulators, it's my impression that almost all initialization errors tend to assume the value to be zero.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


