		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />True, 4-player is listed in <a href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Limitations#Party_multiplayer" class="postlink">Limitations</a>. But perhaps the idea is to contrive game rules to keep all four players from lining up horizontally. Case in point: <em>Warlords</em> ran on a system with even fewer sprites. Or use 8x16s, like <em>Smash TV</em> and <em>Spook-o-Tron</em>. Or use 16-pixel-wide characters and no other sprites, like <em>Super Sprint</em> and <em>Bomberman</em>.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


